caption: Amazing bar! Awesome service!
Incredible.
great vibe, cheap and great paper planes

Travis is amazing, he runs the show like a pro. The French 75 was a special and was made perfectly, $5. Had the chicken popcorn and it’s the best chicken I have ever had, ever. The house made Buffalo sauce and ranch, shut your mouth and just eat it, you won’t regret it.
Great atmosphere! Fun drinks
Service was amazing, and so was the food! Devin was one of the best bartenders I met here.
Intimate space. Great classic drink options. Loved the aesthetics and the service.

We enjoy the cocktails, atmosphere  and food. Try the poutine, that's french fries and gravy with cheese, very good. It's a great starting place or a place to soak up some drinks before heading back to your room.
Cool staff and comfortable space
Great food and drinks!
Chill atmosphere and great mixed drinks! Food is not the best. We got the poutine chips appetizer which was okay, but not amazing.
Biggest sloppy served I've ever seen and delicious. Travis is a hoot, very friendly and comical with good food and cold beer. He needs to add me on facebook.
Always always love Backspace!!! It's the best
Bartender was awesome.   Interesting decor and relatively priced.
Cool literary inspired bar
5 stars
Great bartenders and good Sidecars. It was nice to sit by the fire when it was 35° outside
Jared was awesome best grilled cheese and drinks ever

Great bar.  Quite compared to Bourbon St bars but just as good if not better.   When we came in it was early and not busy.  When we walked in we was greeted and we got to sit wherever we liked.   We ordered some food.  The Burger and fries I got were both delicious and the ranch was some of the best I've had.   She got Fish n chips and it was just as good.    The drinks was really good as well.  You could tell they put alchohol in the drinks unlike other bars in the area.  Highly recommend you walk in and grab a seat order some drinks and food.

This place is a fantastic. Boutique cocktails, extremely friendly, reasonably priced, a fantastic atmosphere makes this a definite stop when you're in New Orleans...hats off to Waites...an impressive bartender
Best burger (get with egg & avocado) I've had in a long time and great atmosphere. I enjoyed being off the main strip for a place I felt welcome and comfortable.
No prices listed on menu menu, website
You can find drinks you will not see in other French Quarter bars. They make special spice drinks. Great people and food is delicious
Great dive bar. Enjoyed. Sazerac was a 10. My wife Paid the highest compliment by having two. Food was good too.
Great vibe. Great food. Great staff
Cozy little bar. Good cocktails.
Great food and atmosphere.  Brandon and Waites were amazing
Outstanding spot for tasty Bar food. i love this place, great food & service. the staff was very helpful and welcoming. like a restaurant in washington i liked.

Nice decor & its cozy. The cocktail menu is very unique, although it's still evident that the craft drinks are inspired by classic cocktails of similar composition. Staff is nice. I'll definitely become a regular when the city is lively again.
Thank you all for making this one of the most enjoyable bar experiences of my life.
Amazing bartender. Hipster Jesus knows his way around green chartreuse. And the fries pair perfectly with the Hemingway dacquiri.
The backspace burger is one of the best I've eaten. My wife got the chips and I got the fries. Both were amazing. The bartenders and staff are friendly and fast to serve. Going back again.
The Koala Infestation is bomb! Waites was super friendly and Joe makes a mean breakfast burrito. Joe also hooked us up with some good food recs!
Loved the custom cocktail, excellent food! Beautiful setting, hidden gem.

Stumbled upon this place today.  This place is a gem just in the French quarter.  Great service, the bartender took care to make my drink right.  Came out perfect 👌.  Food I had Was amazing.  Bloody Mary chicken sandwich, I highly recommend it.  Staff was super friendly.  Stop in I don't think you will regret it. "Here’s to alcohol, the rose-colored glasses of life.” —F. Scott Fitzgerald
Awesome craft cocktails and food in this simple bar.

Found this place on a Monday afternoon and was thoroughly impressed. Great vibe (thanks JJ) and GREAT food! Homemade everything - this is how you build a reputation - with fantastic food. The Burger (wow!) and Chips (homemade and crispy) are amazing!

I’ve only been to NOLA once before, a few years ago, and this place stuck with me. So much so that I almost found it again without nav. The craft cocktails are perfect, the food is delicious and the atmosphere is just the right amount of dark and comfy with friendly staff that treat you like a regular. I wish I WERE a regular!
Nasty

When I say it’s the absolute best burger ever, I mean it is THE BEST BURGER I’ve ever eaten. I skipped all the other restaurants in town to come back just to have to this burger, seriously. The drinks are great, too! Our bartender, Jay, was wonderful and made us feel like family. It felt like I was hanging out with old friends in the quaint and homey atmosphere. Every time I come to New Orleans, I will be back here. I loved every bit of it!

Great little bar, hidden gem in NOLA. Jay J and this brother from another mother in the kitchen made our late lunch experience  perfect. Great cocktails,  solid beer list and amazing service. We hit this place everytime we come to New Orleans.
Great bartenders and company. Authentic New Orleans!

Just not a friendly establishment. The bartender and coworkers get upset when you accidentally steal their seat that they had saved with a pack of cigarettes and then have you kicked out of the bar. Not a good way to end an otherwise nice night in New Orleans. Worse bar experience of my life. Would recommend avoiding.

This might be the worst bar in New Orleans. Service was terrible, drinks were terrible, food was terrible, and prices were terrible. If you are looking for an authentic New Orleans experience, go anywhere else. I highly recommend against.

We spent a couple mid-afternoon hours here as a good change of pace from other French Quarter joints. We enjoyed conversation with the bartender and his suggestions of local brews. Didn’t try any food.
Epic burger and fries and craft cocktails.

Spot on cocktails at a good price. Friendly service and nice ambiance. The poutine chips are in fact potato chips not fries. They were ok but the actual fries (gumbo fries) are great! I got the mystery beer too which was a fun surprise

This bar is AWESOME! We went in because it was quieter than the other bars (even on a Friday night). They have an amazing cocktail menu that is made by the bartenders, and we loved the food. Great bar! Would recommend.
Literary themed and oddly cerebral for the location. Amazing, creative, innovative cocktails...a true diamond in the rough.
Fun bar with great service and creative drinks.
Great food and a really good bloddy mary
Drinks really good. Bartender drinking, only charged for partial bill, when I brought it up.. "that's the price". Awkward
If you don’t have an US id, don't bother coming to this place. What a joke.

We came to this gastropub per Yelp reviews.  It was easy enough to find and the atmosphere is very unique. They have very unusual  drinks and a good selection of local beers. There were 3 bartenders and 8 patrons during our visit.  My DH ordered the burger and I order the Hemingway sandwich. The burger was good but the homemade chips were a bit on the greasy side.  The Hemingway was good but the fries were limp.  We sat at a table and ordered at the bar. When my husband wanted his 2nd beer he ordered it at the bar and after the bartender took his order he proceeded to make a drink for another patron and talk to another.  After a long wait he looked up and scurried down to my husband telling him he was sorry for the wait.  The music was great, the food was OK, but the service needed some improvement.
Amazing place! Custom fancy drinks!
Good selection of home curated libations and beer. Staff was nice, prices were great!

(Translated by Google) I just had lunch, I took the specialty of the house, simply excellent! And the 2 super nice servers!  (Original) Je viens d’y déjeuner, j’ai pris la spécialité de la maison, simplement excellent ! Et les 2 serveurs super sympas !

Bartenders were really cool, atmosphere was very chill. It was on a Wednesday night so it wasn't super busy. Our favorite drink from there would be the Dear Science. Also thought the garlic dry rub boneless chicken were the bomb.
Breakfast for dinner is always appreciated
Stopped here on our way back to the room at the Sheraton, we got our food to go. The backspace burger is a must! So good! Stop here and check them out!

Beware if you eat here... don’t ask for any changes to your meal. No different dressing on your sandwich. Also be sure to order at the bar even if you sit at a table. We found the staff lacked basic customer service skills. The food was mediocre.

Best burger I've ever had. The bread, meat and melty cheese no condiments needed. So good. And the house of love cocktail si damn goos. I had 3 and had a nice little buzz going. Atmosphere is great and bar tenders so nice. Defintely a place i will be stopping again.

Awesome little bar with a good selection of cocktails and local beers. They played some good tunes while I was there - 80s 90s rock. The staff are friendly and happy to provide advice on drink selection. A good escape from the craziness of Bourbon St.
This place is SO relaxing and laid back. The food is phenomenal! The wait staff is very friendly and helpful. A must see!
Fun place
Great tasting food and AMAZING drinks much better for a not so roudy crowd and doesn't smell like the rest of the french quarter. Bar tender was nice and knowledgeable. We will be back soon!
Came here while on travel for work. Bartender was amazing. Good atmosphere and a nice change of pace
Ambiance was awesome, process were on par and service was great. Portions were tiny.
Amazing craft cocktails, food is some of the best I've had in the city.
Late night tasty eats. Comfy seating. The bartender was so charismatic and his drinks are pretty good!
Great atmosphere, creative cocktails, and bar food The bartenders/staff are genuine,  nice, and pleasent to talk to.
Bartender rocked, exactly what I was looking for in New Orleans.

This was next to the quarter house where we stayed on vacation and we ended up here almost every single day! Their bbq Korean chicken skewers were amazing and their burgers are probably the best I’ve had in a long time! Our favorite place of the trip!

I would describe this place as more of a bar  that also serves food. It is dark and on the narrower side and is seat yourself. They had good music though and the food was delicious. I had a burger and my friend had their veggie sandwich. Both were great! My friend was especially pleased since we had been struggling to find a good vegetarian option for her at other restaurants. The bartender was attentive and they had a good beer selection.

Backspace could have gotten 5 stars simply on the fact they pour a proper Dark & Stormy, with Gosling's. The Hemingway was a great late night meal. Atmosphere was very chill, great staff behind the bar and in the kitchen.  I would recommend anyone to go here but I would buy my Misfit Rugby brother and sisters a round.
Nothing to scream about at all! I hope the PO boy.
Food, drinks, service, and atmosphere were all very good. Not as expensive as a lot of places in the quarter, either.
Great Music
Nice burger but terrible pulled pork. Service was good and it's a nice bar if you're stopping in for a drink.
Awesomeness.
Amazing sandwiches!
The pulled pork sliders will make you believe in religion.
Nice little bar. Had a burger and it had to be a good 1/2 pound - couldn’t finish it. Reasonably priced at $12.00.
NO has no shortage of drinkeries but this place has a great vibe, friendly bartender and is out of the way enough to avoid the Bourbon St. crowd.

JM holds this bar down on weeknights in style. We walked in for the first time in a rainy Tuesday and stayed way later than we should have with a belly full of delicious drinks. Have some well-priced Jameson, crack a high life, or order up one of the many top-notch libations they shake up. The writers vibe is a little gimmicky but hey you gotta have your hook. Food is good bang for your buck.
(Translated by Google) Very good food.  (Original) Bardzo dobre jedzenie.

Bartender JM (Janes MICHAEL) was the soul of this nostalgic tavern rife with so much effortless charm: I sat in one of these well worn leather chairs while eating my dinner by the fireplace under a massive stuffed real turkey thankfully that was the only turkey here.  I ordered a drink I swear could jumpstart my electric car called midnight in Paris.  Michael knowing his stuff told me that green chartreuse is 110 proof, and I’m writing this under the influence of green petrol.  Oh geez o forgot to talk about my burger, ok I’m tough and spoiled and picky about my burger: the bun has to have real whole grain, (check) gooey Brie cheese actually melted, (check) sweet carmelized onions (meaning their cooked well but not burnt,) checkmate and I asked for a side of the best tasting brown gravy I have ever had.  Only improvement, coffee, and don’t run out of bread pudding.  Oh since this is also a bar JM didn’t water down my drink he was/is actually more like a barmacist (their charming word) then your average surly better then you bartender.  Once again writing a great review and I will now have to fight you the masses off.  I did my homework seriously and glad I did, plus bonus I !gasp! payed a 1/3 the price got twice the service, was served quickly and it was a beautiful presentation.  I also loved the music of my misspent youth I’m 55.  Your welcome, Terry Davis sent you. Oh hell yes I’m coming back, I’m going to order anything with gravy and an egg and avocado.  Plus the French 75, which as their libations menu explained, that the French 75, was “...a powerful field gun used in World War 1, ...Soxiante Quince in French, was created in 1915.” See your smarter already.  Sonte (cheers in French).
Nice place with a neat selection of locally brewed beers. Very affordable too and cozy vibe. They also have fantastic pictures of great writers that makes you feel in a different time.
Me thy some very friendly people there.
Nice place
Quiet with good service.
Came in this pub on a rainy day. Best cocktails ever from bartender Brandon, the "Blame it on the Voodoo" was timeless and tasty. Decor is eye appealing, will be back soon!

I usually am not picky on food, but this place was pretty bad. The cheese fries were soggy with the cheese really runny. My burger was really undercooked - the middle was still gooey and cold. I asked for medium rare, but it wasn't even cooked. My wife's grilled cheese was also not cooked well. The service was good, though.
Had the Cuban not what I'm used to in Florida

Vegetarian friendly with terrific grilled cheese option. Great authors and typewriters decorate the setting. Friendly staff. Cool author tees for sale with quotes about New Orleans food.  Not overly noisy so you can talk. We dine here every visit to NOLA.
Good late nite eats
Nice local bar. Good food.
Really great, low key spot. Awesome drinks.
Great bar just around the corner from Bourbon St. Staff were friendly and it had a great atmosphere
(Translated by Google) AND MEATLOAF  (Original) MA MEATLOAF

If you go on the weekend, Waits will be there. Waits is the best bartender in the world. Not only that but the vibe in here is top notch, decorated with typewriters and big leather chairs and portraits of the great American authors. It feels like a bar Hemingway could've frequented and I love that.
Surprisingly great bar, great (and hilarious) bartender. Great drinks. We don’t normally stay on this side of the quarter, but we’ll definitely be back to this spot.
Great drinks and friendly bartender!
Fun stop. Not too crazy
We come here for drinks Everytime we come to New Orleans. The Sazerac is a tradition.
Great little place with great bartenders and servers. Some unique libations available. Food was pretty good.

Was there for about 2 hours. Ladies room was out of order so men's room was only option. Impeccably clean and inviting. Great little pub. Drinks were delicious and service was great. Will definitely return next time I am in the area.
Fun environment

Lovely people in a posh little space. We had the Cuban sandwich and the house burger. DH said it was some of the best food he's had in NOLA and we've eat all over for a week! All served with gracious service and a deft bar hand.
Great drinks
Friendly bartender and good food and drink. Prices were good too.
Relaxing place just off the strip... Everyone very friendly and helpful.
Great drinks, enjoyed the 90s alternative music
Good burgers
Good food
Great staff (Brannon) and drinks. Inexpensive drinks  and friendly neighborhood bar. FUN
Great food and very good bartenders.  Nice mellow vibe, had a wonderful time here
This is one of those places that is hard to find, but has excellent specialty drinks and an awesome, hip vibe. Highly recommend. Cheers to the bartender Nathan from Pennsylvania!
Strong drinks and great food. Good prices.
Great food! Great Service! Best burger I have eaten this week in New Orleans! A hidden gem!
One of my favorite places to grab a burger!!!
Excellent staff and music, great environment and cocktails, good food!
Needed more gravy on roast beef poboy
Best burger I've had in forever!
Awesome discovery!  Awesome mixoligists. If you're looking for a cocktail, when they were, this is the place to be and check out. Staff is friendly and warm. A must see.  Definitely a repeat😁
So good. Definitely the best burger ever. The decor is great. Love the exposed beams and the staff was really nice
Great place to go in the quarter after a night of music and Jamisons. Love the grilled cheese. .
Great little bar.  Good food with normal drink prices! If you want to be close to the action but not the tourists... stop by this awesome little place
Good prices good food

Good cocktales (cuz it's book-themed).  On a serious note, great bar and the bartender was very helpful with NOLA recommendations.  Not a typical Bourbon Street party vibe, so it's unique in that sense.
Ask for Brandon. Tell him your favorite liquor and let him work his magic. It might take a few minutes on a busy night, but i guarantee you'll get the best cocktail you have ever had.
Quiet but not too quiet. Great beer selection. The sazerac I had was lovely. Decent prices for a touristy part of the French quarter.
The food and drinks were great, and I loved the atmosphere. My only complaints are that the music was a bit loud, and it took a while to get my food.
Ambiance and food were delicious!!! Drinks are also good!!!! We had a good time in the little place. Quaint and cozy!
Great food and drinks
Very good gastro pub with excellent food, cocktails and setting!
Super cool bar & eatery!
Good place for mild food with sports being played in the tv screens..Sport centred crowd too!!
Interesting small bar with great food and extremely friendly staff.
Good prices and one of the best burgers in the Quarter.
Great service, and a nice change of pace from the craziness of Bourbon St.  Great local beer selection and the burger was really great!  The homemade chips are a great side!
Nice place for soup and a sandwich, not too crowded
Low key. Awesome.
Great spot for reasonable food and fun drinks inspired but some literary greats! Highly recommend!
Hunky bartender making great drinks.
nice place. somewhat limited menu. overall good experience
Poutine!!!! Also great beer selection. All of the food was amazing and the service was outstanding.
Good beers. Nice place in New Orleans.

Ate here Christmas Night, the service was by far the best I have ever seen. Bar tender also covered the tables in a one man show. She was Amazing!!! On top of everything from water refills to just checking on everyone. We would definitely recommend this bar. Merry Christmas!!
Good food and service.  Couple of nice comfy chairs next to a fireplace.

Great little hidden gem. Mixologists create great custom cocktails and the backspace burger is killer. If you're a burger fan this is your selection. Returned another night for the Cuban and it didn't disappoint.
Sandwiches are huge.

(Translated by Google) Just tasty, we had to wait a moment, but there was the drink at the bar for free  (Original) Einfach nur schmackhaft,  wir mussten einen Moment warten,  dafür gab es den Drink an der Bar gratis
Bartender was fantastic, can't recommend this place enough!!
Great atmosphere to just relax and have a drink. There's a nice fireplace and leather chairs. The people are great and the food... THE FOOD!! ITS SOO DAMN GOOOD!!!
Fast and friendly service. All staff were very friendly. The Cuban sandwich was pretty good. And the Sazerac was spot on perfectly made.

Great place to just hang out on a rainy day in NOLA. We go everytime we visit. There are big wingback chairs placed right next to the fireplace. Very cozy when it's cold outside. Nice music, not too loud. Candlelight and low mood lighting. Booths that are the length of the back wall, so you can relax and not worry about having to sit on hard bar stools all night.  Really chill place. Their Moscow Mule and Pim's cup are really good too.  I just realized this post makes me sound really old.  Lol
Excellent food, drinks, and atmosphere!

Seriously just stop by this place if you are in town, you won't be disappointed. We've had Sazeracs in many places, but this place was off the Richter scale. Bartenders were super welcoming, super fast. I'll be back. (Sandwiches were amazing too)
Just stopped and found an outstanding meal
Friendly bar with a variety of beers and spirits. The perfect place to start or end the evening in NOLA

Great bar! We were walking around looking for a place to eat and get a drink until our hotel room was ready. So glad we found this place! Food was delicious and you definitely got your money's worth! Would definitely make it a required stop! The Bloody Mary was stellar! Just the right amount of bite to it!
Great spot for a drink.
Cool bar, good drinks, nice bartender.
Great Bloody Mary.  Cool, cozy joint with some really unique drinks. A great stop in The French Quarter

Nice looking bar. Okay drinks... I don't think old fashioned should get cherry juice, but was nice vibe... Go for quieter times from New Orleans hustle. Don't go there if you don't want to wait for 55 min for food. It's pretty slow .... When I asked for food, they said kitchen is overwhelmed sorry.... After 55 minutes and still no sign of food and I ended up leaving without the food because they said they couldn't make what I ordered due to ingredients not available.
Great cocktails and vibe.
Great little place that's quiet and just off bourbon street. Service was excellent food looked amazing!!
No buy baks....
Love Cassie the bartender!!!!
Ordered drinks and some takeout. Pretty good food for a bar. Great place for late night food if you don't mind the crowds and the wait.
Great atmosphere and great company. Must stop by for a drink whenever in NOLA!

Interesting writers' theme, nice beer selection, friendly bar and kitchen staff. But frankly, it's this place's sandwiches that make it stand out. My personal favorites are the Whitman Roast beef (a roast beef sandwich with fried oysters served on the side, with your choice of roast veggies (my preference) or homemade potato chips as a side item) and the Grown-Up Grilled Cheese (multiple varieties of cheese on toast, with the option of adding bacon; same choice of sides as above). Tends to be quiet when I tent to visit (late afternoons), but frankly I prefer it that way. Recommended.
Good niche food and theme very relaxing place Corey is awesome night bartender and Casey Jo is just as amazing during the day! All mixers are fresh not pre bottled
Loved the food, the atmosphere, the hospitality, and the drinks! ...was there just 2 days ago . The "Backspace Burger" was deeelish.
Enjoyed the bar. Service was great and place was extremely clean. Definitely will go back next time im in new Orleans.
Great bar music & food. We would definitely go back
The Cuban was delicious
Very comfortable venue
Great pub, brilliant atmosphere, staff very friendly
One good experience one poor one
Good food and drinks
Been on vacation in new orleans for a couple of days so far and have found this place enjoyable with a decent beer and great bar staff who are willing to chat

Just spent four days in NOLA for a conference, and this was my go-to bar for the trip. As soon as I arrived I spent a half hour looking for the right "spot", after walking in and out of several nearby bars, this was the place that talked to me.   Ended up getting drinks, a burger one late night, and the poutine app on my last day.  Great food, great beers and specialty drinks, and most importantly:  three different bartenders on three different visits and they were all top notch.  I enjoy a friendly bartender that engages in some small chit chat, even when busy, and your staff hit the nail on the head.  I'll be back on my next visit!

Oh I love this place.  This is more of a local hangout.  The kitchen is open late.  I always stop in here every time I'm in town.  Only complaint I have is basically the same complaint about 90 percent of the places in Nola, the staff is just not treated well by upper management.  One bad review and your fired.
Really nice decor a little more cozy than the bourbon st places. Reasonable prices
Very good burger & nice variety of drinks. Good friendly service. & clean.  Home made chips cooked to order good also.
Great atmosphere and drinks.
Great place for a quiet drink and surprisingly tasty food...try the cajun nachos!

Lovely bar! The atmosphere is a lot different from most bars in New Orleans. This was a bit of a relief for us, a proper bar... The staff is friendly, and easy to talk to. Certainly a place to check out!
Homade chips were delicious the sandwiches were good, tomato basil soup tasted like prego spaghetti sauce...that's not a compliment
This is a fun dive bar with some really good bar food. They also have some fun tees for sale and the drinks are good.
Chillin  atmosphere,  great food , great service
Great cocktails and service. Good prices too.  The bartenders are very friendly.

The atmosphere of this place was pretty neat, however the bartender was not even close to friendly and the rats running across the floor out of the kitchen were pretty disgusting. I’m not kidding. Rats running around the floor. When we asked the bartender about them he replied with “yeah we have traps set for em”.
The only thing better than the service was the food!
I always love this place! I like the staff, the ambience, and the chill vibes. It’s never overly crowded which I love! The Walt Whitman sandwich is one of my favorites in the city!
Good prices for the French Quarter. Decent service.
Delectable craft cocktails. Warm atmosphere and wonderful bartenders. Some of the best cocktails I had during my time in NOLA.

Sandwiches had a lot of bread (maybe that's like saying roller coasters had a lot of hills) and one was very salty. The bartender was great, as was the death in the afternoon. 8/10 would recommend.  Edit: it was the roast beef oyster sandwich. Also, upped to 5 stars because, obviously, this crew really cares.
Perfect, low key spot!!

Like a real-life Cheers this Pub has friendly staff that actually remember you when you return, which is saying a lot in a tourist area  like the French Quarter in New Orleans.  The food was good the beer was excellent and the prices were affordable.
Good spot for locals in the french quater.

This place is fantastic. Small bar but amazing food located at the French quarter very close to my stay at Monteleone hotel. People are so kind and the food quality was high. I ordered the backspace burger with veggie and highly recomend that because of the tender meat and bread quality.
The burger... Its amazing.
Fantastic old school bar. Great drinks at a great price. The menu is simple, but the food is great. It's a must visit place.
Had a great time with the crew working there . Nice and cozy inside
Great service, fantastic drinks, great food, and reasonable prices.

Of all the bars in the French quarter and bourbon Street this one was by far our favorite and the only one we visited twice. Laid back, great vibe and bar tenders were personable and so fun. We even bought a tank top! Thanks for the great place to relax and unwind during our wild and at times tiring weekend! I couldn't give it 5 stars because like most French quarter bars, it was not the freshest place, but still a good place to be.
Fun bar to be at, thr waitress proposed me a good beer, she was super friendly. Didnt try the food though
Didn't try any of the cocktails, but beer and food is fresh and amazing. Recommend to anyone
Cory is a fine tender of the bar. Good music. Decent beer variety
Terrible service! Completely ignored! Won't go back!
Great place to have a few drinks away from the loud and crazy bourbon street.

First time at Backspace and I loved it. The atmosphere is dark but inviting, cozy like a library. The menu is small but there's so many great options. We shared the chicken caprese on ciabetta and the blt with avocado. They were both fantastic but the caprese won out. Portions are huge and extremely well priced. The homemade chips were great. Service was fast and friendly. We'll definitely be back!
Great beer selection, draft and can. Really warm staff. The gumbo was superior compared to Lagasse’s at Dolmenico. I’ll be back and so should you.
Cool lil groovy place the cook that waiting on us was an A+. Get the meatloaf sammich!
Friendly shot gun bar, authors, typewriters, cool.
Favorite bar I found in New Orleans!
Was okay....limited portion also not a fan of eating with plastic silverware.

I love this place. It's super cute with their literary theme! The pricing is reasonable, food and drinks delicious, and the staff were so nice and fun! I highly recommend this place to anyone looking for something unique and maybe a bit different.
Great
Very friendly service and chill atmosphere
Nice bartenders, more of a laid back bar than a drink as much as you can place. Fries are really good.

Why do you have a phone number listed when your staff either can't hear or pretend like they can't hear you over the phone? I had a simple question about the menu and had a woman hang up on me the first time and (not sure if the same woman or not) yell HELLLLLAAAOOO I CANT HEAD YOEUUEE four times the second time and then proceed to keep me on the line listening to the patrons of the bar talking about the randomest things the entire duration of me writing this review (coming up on five minutes now).  Not amused.

Been here for three days and this is this second of many bars that I enjoyed being in. Low key, good drinks in real glasses. Food is a plus since our first didn’t serve food. Price compares to everything up north so no surprises. But after being served full priced drinks in a small Dixie cup ( coyote ugly, ugly) it’s refreshing to spend time in a place that takes care of their clients
Great Bar food !!
Great atmosphere, good food, friendly staff - just a little difficult to get a seat! It's small and seems like it's always busy!
great food!
Great burger for when you get tired of southern food

The food and drinks are great. Staff is really nice. The only problem is the amount of plastic is used there. From dishes to straws (that you don't have the chance to opt out) everything is plastic and non recyclable.
Great food
Nice place to go for a few drinks after work. Great service.. the bartenders do an awesome job..
Rude bartender
Personable bartenders, great food, cool space. A nice place for lunch or a drink.
Great food
Great atmosphere, food, and drinks.
Awesome place. Good food..great staff. Great prices
Fun and good music
Service was unbelievably slow and inattentive.

Speaking personally, Backspace is a great after work spot for service industry people trying to get something a bit nicer than your usual basic bar food. The food is incredible. I had the blt recently with avocado and previously i had their Cuban sandwiche and the Korean bbq skewers. Perfect seasoning and fresh ingredients both lent themselves to my glowing review. The wine selection is good for a small French Quarter bar. I always find something i like. The craft cocktails are probably my favorite aspect of this place, other than the super comfy seating and old hardback books over the fire. Backspace is my new favorite bar in the FQ thus far.
Fun bar good music and specials...
Good food , good vibe, awful staff

I've been on a 4-month work assignment here in NOLA since early November, and I'm happy to call this my go-to bar. Special shout outs to Corey, Siobhan, and Eddie who always took good care of me with both great drinks and great conversation! I probably drank a keg of Guinness and a couple bottles of Caskmates over the past 4 months! Another shout out goes to the guys in the back of the house--all the food I had there was great--I think I tried everything! As my time in NOLA comes to an end, I will genuinely miss this place. I plan on coming back for a bit in the late summer, and will find my way back here I'm sure.  🙏👍😎🍷🍺
It is a nice bar.
Very tasty drinks, and get the meatloaf sandwich.
Great drinks. Wonderful bartender.
I love this place. Great drinks and good food.
Great atmosphere, amazing burgers.

Visiting town for Mardi Gras when we wandered into this cool looking, divey little bar for drinks and a quick bite to eat. Aside from the bartenders being really nice upon walking in and taking our order, that was the extent of the good things to come from this visit. Once we ordered (poutine, Korean BBQ chicken skewers, sliders, and Cuban sandwich) it took OVER AN HOUR to get our food. The food was honestly mediocre at best, especially the skewers which were two puney little pieces of lukewarm chicken. We were warned when we walked in that the kitchen had run out of a lot of stuff due to the festivities so the menu was limited, but this is absolutely unacceptable. The only reason I'm giving two stars is because the bartenders we're both very apologetic and comped a good portion of the tab.

Spent the week at the Marriott across the street for a conference and brought everyone here to wind down several nights. Great drinks, reasonable prices, amazing bartenders! Eddie, Corey, and Michael were awesome and took great care of everyone. Thanks for providing a perfect place for us to all catch up and hang out!
After evening spot to get a good drink and great food! The bread is awesome.
great drinks

When you're closing the bar at night...  Alone...  You are very aware that you are really not alone.  They all died.  Great place for a zazarac
Meatloaf sandwich will make your stomach happy!!
The vibe here was fantastic. Great atmosphere. Good classic cocktails.

This is my favorite spot to hit after work. I bartend and its hard to find a place with good food and not a bunch of degenerates after we close at 1. This place is it. Relaxed, good music, a fireplace when its cold, tv's, and a Cory, who is the greatest. Hate to talk about this hidden gem because I want it all to myself but I want dollars to head their way.
Friendly, great atmosphere, tasty food and excellent cocktails!
This is one of my favorite bars in the city. They have $3 Yuengling and friendly as hell bartenders. I don't think I have to say anymore.
Amazing gumbo

YUM! GRILLED CHEESE!

Maybe I read too much into their reviews but it's still just a bar and not a place where you can actually sit and write. *shrug* The food was decent.
A very cool dive bar with a cozy hometown feel and cheap drinks. Corey D. is a legend behind the bar. He handled 50 patrons alone, without batting an eye.

This was a real cool and mellow place. We went during the week of New Year's. Good music, and surprisingly good food. The staff was attentive and friendly. Would definitely go back if there's a return trip to New Orleans.
Good place for visitors to try out. Very close to the French quarter and they have good spirit. Drinks are nice and relatively cheaper. They have a good environment too.

Coming from LA this is a cool place. Music, drinks pretty good. The Cajun Poutine was like stew nachos. Great for cold weather. For a writer bar the Tv's and video poker ruin the authenticity but the fireplace is a nice touch.  Again great for winter.
Not the cheapest place, but worth the price for the atmosphere. Sophisticated and with a delicious kitchen that is usually open late night. A favorite place to stop after work or a rough day.
Menu was interesting and food was generally good. The “for writers” vibe was a little damaged by the hockey games on TV but I like what they were going for at least.
Late Night Yumms!
Good beer, great food plus they were great with my wife's allergies.  Go for a Hemingway Cuban.
